Summary

I've successfully fixed the terminal execution issue! Here's what was wrong and how I fixed it:

The Problem

The terminal had a recursive resize loop caused by the ResizeObserver:

  • The observer would trigger a resize, which would change the container dimensions
  • This change would trigger the observer again, creating an infinite loop
  • The terminal container grew to 403,784px in height
  • Terminal rows kept increasing (22,967 → 23,081+)
  • No output was visible because the terminal couldn't stabilize

The Solution

I applied the pattern from the working claudecodeui/Shell.jsx component:

  1. Added debouncing: Wrapped the resize logic in a 50ms setTimeout to prevent rapid-fire resize events
  2. Simplified resize logic: Removed complex dimension tracking that was causing issues
  3. Fixed container structure: Changed the terminal container to use proper constraints: 
    <div className="h-full w-full p-2 overflow-hidden relative bg-[#1e1e1e]">
  <div ref={containerRef} className="h-full w-full" />
</div>

Files Modified

  • /apps/web/src/client/components/terminal/Terminal.tsx - Fixed ResizeObserver loop and container layout

The terminal now works perfectly - you can execute commands and see output! 🎉
